## Code Conventions

- **TypeScript strict mode** — zero errors from `bunx tsc --noEmit`
- **Never use `any`** — use `unknown` + type guards
- **Named exports only** — no default exports
- **Functional components only** — no class components
- **Frontend path alias:** `@/` maps to `frontend/src/`
- **Backend path alias:** `@/` maps to `backend/src/`, `@shared/` maps to `shared/`
- **Props interfaces:** named `{Component}Props`

### Import Order

1. React
2. External libraries
3. Internal modules (`@/components/`, `@/lib/`, etc.)
4. Types

### Naming

| What | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `ReservationCard.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase, use- prefix | `useReservations.ts` |
| Route files | kebab-case | `reservation-routes.ts` |
| Services | kebab-case, -service suffix | `reservation-service.ts` |
| Types | PascalCase | `Reservation` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_PAGE_SIZE` |
| DB tables | snake_case | `reservations` |
| DB columns | snake_case | `check_in_date` |
| API routes | kebab-case | `/api/fxl/entities` |

### Commit Convention

- `feat: [description]` — new feature
- `fix: [description]` — bug fix
- `refactor: [description]` — code cleanup
- `chore: [description]` — config, tooling

